node.text:
Stüssy Boucherouite T-shirt Rugs

Stüssy has collaborated with the Artisan Project, a Women’s Weaving Cooperative in Ain Leuh, Morocco, on a collection of upcycled boucherouite t-shirt rugs.

Imperfect archival t-shirts from the Stüssy warehouse in Irvine, California, were used as the base material for the weavers to construct each design. Painterly gestures, 
Californian landscapes, surfboards, and vintage Moroccan carpets were referenced in the creation of each piece. 

This release marks the beginning of a recurring 
relationship with Artisan Project. 

30 unique t-shirt rugs will be available exclusively on stussy.com and regional sites on September 3rd at 10am local time.
